Japanese title: Buryū Sōdatsusen! 〜Gekitotsu, Shibusen bāsesu Arakunofobia?〜 (BREW争奪戦! 〜激突、死武専vsアラクノフォビア?〜)

War erupts in a frozen wasteland! An army of DWMA staff, Weapons, and Meisters battle the forces of Arachnophobia for control of Brew, the greatest of Eibon’s creations.
name: The Battle for Brew - Clash: the DWMA vs. Arachnophobia?

description:
Japanese title: Arashi no Mosukīto! 〜Arishi hi no Sekai, Seigen Jikan wa Jū-pun?〜(嵐のモスキート! 〜在りし日の世界、制限時間は10分?〜)

Maka, Black Star, Death the Kid, and their Weapons engage Mosquito within the magnetic field. With even their strongest attacks falling short, Soul is forced to consider a risky move.
name: Mosquito's Storm! Ten Minutes to Fight in the World of the Past?

description:
Japanese title: Hanate, Shichi-nin no Kyōmei Rensa! 〜Hakai to Sōzō no Ensōkai?〜 (放て、7人の共鳴連鎖! 〜破壊と創造の演奏会?〜)

Soul’s gamble pays off, allowing a magnificent display of resonance against Mosquito and unlocking unseen levels of power within Maka. But it might not be enough to keep Brew out of the wrong hands.
name: Unleash the Seven's Resonance Link! A Recital of Destruction and Creation?

description:
Japanese title: Meitantei Daiichi no Jiken 〜Kiddo ga Abaku Shibusen no Himitsu?〜 (名探偵第一の事件 〜キッドが暴く死武専の秘密?〜)

Following the battle to claim Brew, Arachne moves forward with her plan, and the students of DWMA try to recover from defeat. Meanwhile, Death the Kid confronts Dr. Stein with some burning questions.
name: The Detective's First Case - Kid Exposes the DWMA's Secret?

description:
Japanese title: Shura e no Yūwaku 〜Biggu na Otoko no Osaerarenai Iradachi?〜 (修羅への誘惑 〜ビッグな男の抑えられない苛立ち?〜)

Death the Kid’s dealing with a lot: he suspects Joe’s involved with the Magic Tools mystery, and he’s forced into yet another brutal fight with depressed Black Star.
name: Asura's Temptation - The Big Man's Uncontrollable Irritation?

description:
Japanese title: Kurona, Tōbō 〜Kudasai, Kimi no Hohoemi?〜 (クロナ、逃亡 〜ください、君の微笑み?〜)

Arachne risks her life to gain a new ally in the plot against DWMA. Meanwhile, when Crona runs away from the school, Maka sets out to bring her friend back safely.
name: Crona's Escape - Show Me Your Smile, Please?

description:
Japanese title: Kirareta Kādo 〜Medyūsa, Shibusen ni Tōkō Suru?〜 (切られたカード 〜メデューサ、死武専に投降する?〜)

Medusa offers Death a deal: in exchange for her release, she’ll reveal the Kishin’s location. The Grim Reaper won’t have long to decide - Arachne is on the verge of releasing madness on a global scale!
name: The Cards are Cut - Medusa Surrenders to the DWMA?

description:
Japanese title: Kurukuru Kururu 〜Hakase wa Odoru, Atarashiki Sekai?〜 (クルクルクルル 〜博士は踊る、新しき世界?〜)

Dr. Stein’s mind is deteriorating quickly. As he explores his mental landscape for a way out of the increasing madness, Crona begs Death for a chance to right past wrongs.
name: Twirl 'Round and 'Round - A New World in Which the Doc Dances?

description:
Japanese title: Shingeki! Baba Yagā no Shiro 〜Nanka Moyamoya Suru?〜 (進撃! ババ･ヤガーの城 〜なんかモヤモヤする?〜)

The forces of DWMA prepare to open several fronts in the war against Arachnophobia - but Maka decides the time has arrived to fight a very personal battle of her own design!
name: Charge Baba Yaga's Castle! Things are Kind of Gloomy?

description:
Japanese title: Saigo no Madōgu 〜Buki Nashi Kiddo no Misshon Inposshiburu?〜 (最後の魔道具 〜武器無しキッドのミッションインポッシブル?〜)

Maka and Soul continue their search for Medusa’s lair. Meanwhile, a clash with the creepy guardians of the final Magic Tool leaves Death the Kid even more suspicious of his father’s true motives.
name: The Last Magic Tool - Mission Impossible for Unarmed Kid?

description:
Japanese title: Yowamushi Kurona no Ketsui 〜Itsumo Soba ni Ite Kureta Kimi ni?〜 (弱虫クロナの決意 〜いつもそばにいてくれた君に?〜)

Physical pain and mental anguish are guaranteed when Crona and Marie enter the treacherous confines of Medusa’s lair to confront the little witch and the insane Dr. Stein.
name: Weakling Crona's Determination - For You, for Always Being by My Side?

description: Thousands of people across Brooklyn have slipped into a mysterious coma, including Chas' (Charles Halford) daughter. John (Matt Ryan) must find and defeat the evil behind it before it consumes the city.
name: Quid Pro Quo

description:
Japanese title: Taima no Hachō 〜Mōkō, Ikari no Majin Gari?〜 (退魔の波長 〜猛攻、怒りの魔人狩り?〜)

Crona is forced to make the ultimate sacrifice as the battle against Medusa rages on. If the witch is to be destroyed, and Dr. Stein saved, Maka and Soul must reach rare heights of power.
name: Anti-Magic Wavelength - Fierce Attack, the Anger-Filled Genie Hunter?

description: Manny (Harold Perrineau) sends John to help an old friend, Ritchie Simpson (guest star Jeremy Davies), at Ivy University, where a group of students have a found a way into an alternate dimension only to be met by a maniacal killer (guest star William Mapother).
name: A Whole World Out There

description:
Japanese title: Bu ka Shura ka 〜Kessen, Mifune bāsesu Burakku Sutā?〜 (武か修羅か 〜決戦、ミフネvsブラック☆スター?〜)

The final confrontation between Black Star and Mifune begins! As the warriors clash, Mifune reveals a startling connection to the young Meister’s past.
name: Warrior or Slaughterer? Showdown: Mifune vs. Black Star?

description: Finn has an out-of-body experience that takes him all over Ooo and beyond.
name: Astral Plane

description: When inventor Elon Musk lands in Springfield, he and Homer become fast friends and revolutionize the town's nuclear plant. But when Musk goes overboard and Mr. Burns wants him removed, Homer must figure out a way to break up with him.
name: The Musk Who Fell To Earth

description: The Titans decide they should keep an eye on Nibor, the Bizzaro World's Robin, when he arrives in Jump City.
name: Robin Backwards

description:
Japanese title: Kiseki no Chabudaigaeshi 〜Bokura no Desu Shitī Robo?〜 (奇跡のちゃぶ台返し 〜僕らのデス･シティーロボ?〜)

After the fight between Black Star and Mifune ends, the DWMA gains a powerful new ally. And when Death utilizes Brew in an astounding way, he turns the tides of the battle against Arachnophobia.
name: The Miraculous Coffee Table Flip - Fly, Our Death City Robot?

description:
Japanese title: Desusaizu o Motta Shinigami-sama 〜Chotto Saki wa Yami Darake?〜 (武器(デスサイズ)を持った死神様 〜一寸先はヤミだらけ?〜)

The Kishin and the Grim Reaper tear into each other with unimaginable levels of power. Before this ultimate clash between good and evil concludes, great sacrifices will be made.
name: Lord Death Wields a Death Scythe - Just One Step from Utter Darkness?

description:
Japanese title: Ashura Kakusei 〜Sekai no Ikitsuku Hate e?〜 (阿修羅覚醒 〜世界の行き着く果てへ?〜)

Arachnophobia is crumbling, but the Kishin is stronger than ever. Maka, Death the Kid, Black Star, and their Weapons attack with all their might, but when Soul slips into unconsciousness, all could be lost.
name: Asura Wakes - To the End of the World?
